full_text: @MHChat If we are true + authentic with ourselves first we are more likely to be able to be able to accept who we are. If we can't + run away from it, it can negatively affect our #mentalhealth and self esteem and lead to more issues, potentially self harm, trust issues, paranoia #mhchat

full_text: @MHChat #mhchat I think it's down to the individual on social media how much of yourself you speak about. It can be good because talking about your  experience of mental health issues/treatment can help break the stigma down and encourage others to talk more. I found this happened.
full_text(utf-8): b"@MHChat #mhchat I think it's down to the individual on social media how much of yourself you speak about. It can be good because talking about your  experience of mental health issues/treatment can help break the stigma down and encourage others to talk more. I found this happened."

full_text: @MHChat I think there is. If there is a space where you can safely be vulnerable and therefore comfortably be authentic then maybe self worth can be built up. If you aren't able to be truly yourself authentically you can lose confidence, identity and have low self worth #mhchat
full_text(utf-8): b"@MHChat I think there is. If there is a space where you can safely be vulnerable and therefore comfortably be authentic then maybe self worth can be built up. If you aren't able to be truly yourself authentically you can lose confidence, identity and have low self worth #mhchat"

full_text: @MHChat @MackenzieLitt13 Good question! Being honest with ourselves when things are going both well and not so well is important. Sometimes I do think we have to say to ourselves, that something doesn't feel good and I need to address this because I know the consequences.
full_text(utf-8): b"@MHChat @MackenzieLitt13 Good question! Being honest with ourselves when things are going both well and not so well is important. Sometimes I do think we have to say to ourselves, that something doesn't feel good and I need to address this because I know the consequences."

full_text: @MHChat I think it's to leave some parts out - then it leaves  a certain ambiguity. I think a lot of people are afraid of being truly authentic and so hide pieces of themselves, for an example when phoning in sick for work because of anxiety, but say you have a severe headache.
full_text(utf-8): b"@MHChat I think it's to leave some parts out - then it leaves  a certain ambiguity. full_text: @MHChat #mhchat authenticity is to be true to who you really are. To lack authenticity is to knowingly lie, deceive or distort information about yourself to serve a purpose... However this sometimes can be to protect yourself e.g against stigma
